<Base title="About" description="Power systems analysis, reinforcement learning, and open-source tools.">
  <h1>Hi, I'm <span class="accent-gradient">Alfie</span></h1>

  <p>
    I work on power systems analysis, grid constraint modelling, and
    reinforcement learning for energy dispatch.
  </p>

  <p>
    I built an <a href="https://alfiemcglennon.github.io/gb-grid-tool/">open-source interactive tool</a>
    for exploring GB transmission constraints — DC power flow, LP dispatch, and
    ERA5 weather data, all running in the browser. It's validated against NESO
    published boundary transfer data and solves constrained dispatch using HiGHS
    compiled to WebAssembly.
  </p>

  <p>
    Currently exploring how RL agents can learn network-constrained dispatch
    from experience — training topology-aware agents with 109 continuous actions
    across 27 zones to approximate what LP solvers compute analytically.
  </p>
</Base>
